  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Mosquito-borne flavivirus\nOne of the most common causes of\nencephalitis\nglobally\nHighly endemic in parts of Asia and the Western Pacific\nUp to 70,000 cases, 15,000 deaths annually\nUsually affects children in endemic areas, as most adults have been exposed and are immune\nRare in tourists, as the vector\nCulex\nmosquito breeds primarily in rural rice paddies",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "encephalitis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Encephalitis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "5-15 day incubation\nSudden, high\nfever\nHeadache\nNuchal rigidity and other meningeal signs\nSeizure\n(especially in infants)\nVarious pyramidal and extrapyramidal signs",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
